-- Trump says no deals in the works to sell casinos
-- 
-- Fri Apr 4, 2008 4:40pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/04/04/us-trumpentertainment-idUSWNAS692520080404

 

 LOS ANGELES  (Reuters) - Trump Entertainment Resorts Inc TRMP.O said on Friday it remains focused on its strategic plan for operating, and improving performance at all of its casino hotels, including completing the new tower at the Trump Taj Mahal in Atlantic City, New Jersey. 

 The company also said it is looking at opportunities to sell one or more of its other properties and, from time to time, engages in discussions with third parties regarding proposals to acquire company properties. At this time, the company is not party to any agreement to sell any of its casino hotel properties, the company said. (Reporting by Deena Beasley; Editing by  Tim Dobbyn )